WHEREAS, under the leadership of Police Chief Richard Catlett, a Pigeon Forge native,
the police department recently received its second Law Enforcement Accreditation Award from
the Tennessee Association of Police Chiefs; and
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we specially recognize the members of the Pigeon
Forge Police Department for their professional devotion and steadfast commitment to protecting
and serving their community while upholding the law and preserving the peace; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate and applaud Police Chief Richard Catlett and the Pigeon
Forge Police Department on winning the Excellence in Police Services Award from the
Tennessee Municipal League and extend our gratitude for the department's steadfast service to
the law and the citizens and visitors of Pigeon Forge.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
